  "@type": "SolutionRecord",
  "@id": "ocp:github/zrythm--zrythm",
  "meta": {
    "title": "zrythm",
    "description": "a highly automated and intuitive digital audio workstation - official mirror",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-03T10:27:20.510Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-03T10:27:20.510Z",
    "keywords": [
      "audio",
      "computer-music",
      "cpp",
      "cpp23",
      "daw",
      "juce",
      "midi",
      "music",
      "music-composition",
      "music-production",
      "qml",
      "qt6"
    ],
    "license": "NOASSERTION"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "- Object looping, cloning, linking and stretching\n- Adaptive snapping\n- Multiple lanes per track\n- Bounce anything to audio or MIDI\n- Piano roll (MIDI editor) with chord integration, drum mode and a lollipop velocity editor\n- Audio editor with part editing (including in external app) and adjustable gain/fades\n- Event viewers (list editors) with editable object parameters\n- Per-context object functions\n- Audio/MIDI/automation recording with options to punch in/out, record on MIDI input and create takes\n- Device-bindable parameters for external control\n- Wide variety of track types for every purpose\n- Signal manipulation with signal groups, aux sends and direct anywhere-to-anywhere connections\n- In-context listening by dimming other tracks\n- Automate anything using automation events or CV signal from modulator plugins and macro knobs\n- Detachable views for multi-monitor setups\n- Searchable preferences\n- Support for LV2/CLAP/VST2/VST3/AU/LADSPA/DSSI plugins, SFZ/SF2 SoundFonts, Type 0 and 1 MIDI files, and almost every audio file format\n- Flexible built-in file and plugin browsers\n- Optional plugin sandboxing (bridging)\n- Stem export\n- Chord pad with built-in and user presets, including the ability to generate chords from scales\n- Automatic project backups\n- Undoable user actions with serializable undo history\n- Hardware-accelerated UI\n- SIMD-optimized DSP\n- Cross-platform, cross-audio/MIDI backend and cross-architecture\n- Available in multiple languages including Chinese, Japanese, Russian, Portuguese, French and German",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
